<UserControl x:Name="___No_Name_" x:Class="WpfApp1.IntrestingFactsAboutLebanonUserControl"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:WpfApp1" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=netstandard"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             d:DesignHeight="570" d:DesignWidth="1055" Background="#FF191818">
            <!--#003366-->
    <Grid>
        <TextBlock Text="Here are some interesting facts about Lebanon:" Margin="0 15 5 10" FontSize="26" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Foreground="#FF33D6FF" />
        <ListBox Margin="20 20 20 20" Background="#FF191818" HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" >
            <ListBox.ItemTemplate >
                <DataTemplate>
                    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal" Margin="0 0 5 10">
                        <TextBlock Text="&#8226;" Margin="0 0 5 10" FontSize="18" VerticalAlignment="Center" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Foreground="#FF33D6FF" />
                        <TextBlock Text="{Binding}" Width="930" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="15" Foreground="#FF33D6FF" VerticalAlignment="Center" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                    </StackPanel>
                </DataTemplate>
            </ListBox.ItemTemplate>
            <ListBox.Items>
                <sys:String>Lebanon is one of the oldest inhabited countries in the world, with evidence of human presence dating back over 7,000 years.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Lebanon is known as the Land of the Cedars due to its iconic cedar trees, which are featured on the country's flag.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Beirut, the capital of Lebanon, was once known as the Paris of the Middle East for its vibrant cultural scene and cosmopolitan atmosphere.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Lebanon is home to a diverse population, consisting of various religious and ethnic groups, including Maronite Christians, Sunni and Shia Muslims, and Druze.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>The Lebanese cuisine is renowned worldwide for its delicious flavors and variety. It includes popular dishes like hummus, falafel, tabbouleh, and shawarma.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Byblos, an ancient city in Lebanon, is one of the oldest continuously inhabited cities in the world and is recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Lebanon has a rich history of winemaking, with vineyards dating back thousands of years.
 The country produces a wide range of wines, especially in the Bekaa Valley region.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>The Baalbek Temple complex in Lebanon is a remarkable archaeological site and is home to some of the largest Roman ruins in the world, including the Temple of Jupiter.</sys:String>
                <sys:String>Lebanon has a diverse landscape that includes beautiful coastline, snow-capped mountains, fertile valleys, and picturesque villages.</sys:String>
            </ListBox.Items>
        </ListBox>
    </Grid>
</UserControl>
